2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a mixed one-bit compressive sensing method, which is based on recent progress in one-bit compressive sensing and involves information theory concepts such as signal recovery and measurement acquisition. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with image reconstruction and correction, which is a common task in multimedia processing. 
4. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper proposes an iterative algorithm for the mixed one-bit compressive sensing method, which involves numerical analysis techniques such as optimization and linear algebra. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - Although less likely, the paper could fall under this category as it deals with information acquisition and processing in a network of measurements (regular and saturated).
